<p>October 1915</p>
<p>Monday 4</p>
<p>"Shell Green" dressing station for 24 hrs duty. Received letter from Prof. Helmy of Cairo &amp; letter from J.W.Holt !</p>
<p>6 casualties up till sunset, all resulting from a violent artillery attack in the morning.</p>
<p>The shells burst all round the dressing station &amp; there was a constant rain of pellets &amp; lumps of [indecipherable] all round, right up to the very the door of the shed.</p>
<p>Demonstration at 8.15 p.m. with vast amount of artillery &amp; lot of rifle fire but no casualties (only a sham).</p>
